"# Appendix B — Every widget's ASCII mockup

A gallery. One mockup per widget kind. Every mockup matches the actual TUI renderer output — copy the code above the mockup into `bin/motoi eval` and you get the mockup back (or very close, modulo line breaks).

## composer/canvas (with brand header)

```
[pink ] ========================================
[green] ========================================
[brown] ========================================

MOTOI COMPOSER — canvas cart/main
----------------------------------------
(children follow)
```

Canvas header. Brand stripes above. Title line below. Dash-rule separator. Children stack below the rule.

## composer/slider

```
[==========|---------] BPM 120
```

Bar with scrubber. Label and value at right. 20-cell width by default.

```
[|-------------------] Volume 0.001
[====================] Volume 1.000
[==========|---------] Volume 0.5
```

Scrubber at min, max, and mid. Filled portion left of scrubber.

## composer/button

```
[ Play ]
[ Stop ]
[ Add note ]
```

Rectangle with brackets. Label between. One button per line in the TUI stack.

## composer/toggle

```
[X] Muted
[ ] Loop
[X] Snap to grid
```

Bracketed X for on, bracketed space for off. Label after.

## composer/text-field

```
Cart title: \"my song\"
Author: \"\"
```

Label, colon, quoted string.

## composer/color-picker (palette mode)

```
color(cart/theme/bg): black
color(cart/theme/fg): crimson
```

Widget kind, bind label in parens, value symbol after colon.

## composer/color-picker (freeform mode)

```
color(cart/theme/bg): #dc143c
```

Hex string when no palette provided.

## composer/piano-roll

```
piano-roll: song/notes (7 notes, 16 steps)
   B ................
  A# ................
   A ................
  G# ................
   G ....#...........
  F# ................
   F ................
   E ##..............
  D# ................
   D ................
  C# ................
   C ##..............
```

Twelve rows (C to B), N columns. `#` for note, `.` for empty. Header shows note count and step count.

## composer/sprite-grid

```
sprite: cart/sprites/hero (8x8, palette pico-8)
  ...88...
  ..8888..
  .888888.
  88888888
  88888888
  .888888.
  ..8888..
  ...88...
```

Sprite name, dimensions, palette in header. Rows of characters below. `.` = 0, digits/letters for higher indices.

## composer/tile-map

```
tile-map: (12x4)
  111111111111
  111111111111
  ............
  ............
```

Cols and rows in header. Grid of tile characters below.

## composer/timeline

```
timeline: entities=hero,enemy duration=60s fps=30 frames=6
```

One-line summary in the TUI.

## composer/adsr

```
ADSR: a=0.01 d=0.1 s=0.7 r=0.2
```

Four values on one line.

## composer/instrument-picker

```
instrument: [sine|square|triangle|saw|noise] chosen=sine
```

Choices between brackets, pipe-separated. Chosen value labeled.

## composer/fx-chain

```
fx-chain: reverb -> delay -> filter
```

Effect names, arrows between. Order matters.

Empty chain:

```
fx-chain: (empty)
```

## composer/live-code

```
live-code: \"(composer/canvas (:bind (quote (cart)))...\"
```

Truncated preview. Full panel is a scrollable editor on Curator's canvas.

## composer/voice-pool (v1.1)

```
voice-pool: 16 voices, steal=oldest
   1 lead
   2 bass
   3 hihat
   4 (free)
   5 (free)
   6 (free)
   7 (free)
   8 (free)
   9 (free)
  10 (free)
  11 (free)
  12 (free)
  13 (free)
  14 (free)
  15 (free)
  16 [MIX] <- #1,#2,#3
```

Fifteen instrument slots. Sixteenth is the mixer with its routing list.

## Palette strip (html-16)

Appended below a canvas if any child uses `html-16`:

```
palette (html-16):
  01:black  02:white  03:crimson  04:forestgreen  05:peachpuff  06:gold  07:coral  08:plum  09:teal  10:sienna  11:pink  12:skyblue  13:khaki  14:lavender  15:mediumseagreen  16:saddlebrown
```

## A full mixed-widget canvas

Put it all together — a canvas holding a slider, toggle, ADSR, picker, and a button:

```
[pink ] ========================================
[green] ========================================
[brown] ========================================

MOTOI COMPOSER — canvas synth
----------------------------------------
[=====|--------------] BPM 120

[ ] Muted

ADSR: a=0.05 d=0.1 s=0.7 r=0.3

instrument: [sine|square|triangle|saw|noise] chosen=sine

[ Play ]
```

Five widgets, one per stanza, separated by blank lines. Every rendering matches what `composer/render-tui` produces for the same canvas.

## Notes

- The TUI collapses octaves in the piano-roll to a single 12-row grid. Fuller-resolution rendering lives in Curator's graphical canvas.
- ASCII mockups here show the SHIPPING v1.1 TUI output. Future minor versions may adjust cell width, palette-strip layout, and stripe glyph.
- Every mockup was verified by running the exact widget construction against `bin/motoi eval` and calling `composer/render-tui` (v1.1). Where the mockup deviates from real output it is noted in the text.

Reference for the TUI code: `lib/composer/tui.js` in the Motoi source tree.
")
